snippet.textDisplay: Tanking doesn't always work. The Raptors tanked for 20 years and were garbage, then Masai came along made a couple of key trades, and made the playoffs in his first year. Then he drafted guys like pascal siakam at 27, OG anonouny at 22, norman Powell at at 29, traded Terrence Ross who was a high draft pick for veteran guys like ibaka, and made a championship team. Tanking is overrated, it works once or twice out of every 10 attempts. The other thing is, even when you get those players that you tanked for its hard to teach them how to win when you have a losing culture.while your getting those players how you gonna teach them how to win when there losing 70 games a year. That's why the sixers suck, even with embid and Simmons, you couldn't teach them how to win cause you never had a winning culture, whole the raps taught guys like siakam and Powell how to win cause they had a winning culture. That stuff matters

snippet.textDisplay:
Problem with the 'process' is how the Sixers did it. They tanked for like 5 straight seasons. and kept getting players with injury concerns. So? they got Micheal Carter-Williams in 2013, guess what? he was ROTY. Then what did they do? traded him away???
They draft Joel Embiid, coming off injury, in 2014. Sat out the whole rookie season. Has been good lately, but still injury concerns. I wouldnt have drafted Embiid. I would have gone for Aaron Gordon or tried to trade to get Jabari Parker.
2015, they wind up with Jahil Okafor. did good his rookie season, but then was given up on after that when Embiid came in.
But just go back, they keep Micheal Carter-Williams, develop him, and then get Aaron Gordon the next draft, that would have made them better.
